    "millsfield:images_texts": [
      "DELTA\nGELTA\nCELTA",
      "POSTCARD\nMEET THE STARS OF THE DELTA FLEET. Three major aircraft types form the\nnucleus of Delta's modern fleet of jets:\nThe wide-bodied Lockheed L-1011 TriStar, a 264 passenger airplane\npowered by three Rolls-Royce RB211-22B engines, has a cruising speed of\nalmost 600 miles per hour and a range of over 2100 statute miles. Three pilots\nand eight flight attendants make up the TriStar crew.\nThe Wide-Ride'™ Boeing 727-232, Delta's major medium-range jet has a range\nof over 1500 statute miles. With comfortable seating for 135 people, the 727 has\na cruising speed of over 550 miles per hour and carries a crew of three pilots\nand four flight attendants.\nThe Douglas DC-9-32 was designed to operate on shorter-haul routes, with a\nrange of over 1100 statute miles and a cruising speed of 530 miles per hour.\nThe 90-passenger DC-9 has a crew of two pilots and three flight attendants.\nPLACE\nSTAMP\nHERE\nDELTA IS READY WHEN YOU ARE!\n0432-01338\nPrinted U.S.A\n2015.166.2523"
    ],
